- Transformations

what are Transformations  ? This is one kind of css syntax which will manipulate an element's size,shape, position etc.

syntax
    selector {
        transform: transform-func
    }

    Below are the in-built transform functions

    translate(x,y) 
    translateX(20px)
    translateY(30px)
    scale(2)
    scaleX(2)
    scaleY(2)
    rotate(45deg)

- Transitions

what are transitions ? This will let you animate the changes smoothly over time instead of instantly.

    syntax
        selector {
            transition: property/transform-name transition-duration transition-func transition-delay
        }

 Assignment - Will transitions applies to all the properties or not ?

- Animations

First we have to define the animation using @keyframes

syntax 

    selector {
        animation-name: <animation-name>;
        animation-duration: 5s
    }

    we can use shorthand 

    selector {
        animation: name duration timing-function delay iteration-count direction fill-mode;
        }

    @keyframes bgcolorchange {
  from {
    background-color: red;
  }
  to {
    background-color: cadetblue;
  }
}

instead of from, to we can use % 

@keyframes bgcolorchange {
  10% {
    background-color: red;
  }
  30% {
    background-color: cadetblue;
  }
  60% {
    background-color: black;
  }
  100% {
    background-color: violet;
  }
}

